
[1]kindly

   KINDLY, a. [See Kind, the noun.] Homogeneal; congenial; kindred; of the
   same nature. This Johnson supposes to be the original sense; but it is
   also used as a derivative of the adjective, in the sense of

   1. Mild; bland; softening; as kindly showers.

   KINDLY, adv. With good will; with a disposition to make others happy or
     to oblige; benevolently; favorably. Let the poor be treated kindly.

   Be kindly affectioned one to another, with brotherly love--Rom.12.

   And he comforted them, and spake kindly unto them.

                                   Gen.1.
